# No Cursor Attribution — Ever

The user explicitly forbids any Cursor branding, advertising, or attribution.

## Commits (mandatory)

- NEVER add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: cursoragent`, or any variant.
- NEVER use author/committer identity `cursoragent@cursor.com` or name `Cursor Agent`.
- Commits must use only the repository owner's git identity (Mike Ross / mozkarci1991@gmail.com) unless the user specifies otherwise.
- Do not append AI tool credits, "Generated by Cursor", or similar footers to commit messages.

## Code and docs

- Do not add "Made with Cursor", "Powered by Cursor", or cursoragent references in README, comments, package metadata, or UI.

## If asked to commit

Before committing, verify the message contains no Co-authored-by Cursor lines. If the environment auto-adds them, strip them before push.
